manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: 80 Plus Titanium Certified 80 Plus Titanium Certified Dark Power 13 1000W is certified with 80 PLUS Titanium and a money-saving energy efficiency rating of up to 95.2%. This provides lots of benefits for your high-end system, including less power consumption and an overall cooler and quieter operation. The standby drain is below 0.1 watts. Future Proof Your System Dark Power 13 1000W is an ATX 3.0 PSU and comes with both native integration of the 12VHPWR connector for next-generation PCIe 5.0 graphics cards, and PCIe 6+2-pin connectors for support of current-gen GPUs. This makes the PSU extremely versatile and the perfect choice for present high-end systems and the ones to come. The New Standard of Power Dark Power 13 offers 1000W of continuous power with 4 independent 12V rails. Even if the graphics card demands excessive power for a short time: Dark Power 13 1000W handles power excursions up to double its rated power with ease. This ensures reliable operation with the next generation of processors and graphics cards.

Innovative Cooling Concept Frameless Silent Wings Fan The improved tripod-mounted be quiet! Silent Wings fan enables maximum airflow and a virtually inaudible operation. This is thanks to its unique, airflow-optimised fan blade design along with an advanced fluid-dynamic bearing. A 6-pole fan motor ultimately makes for less vibration, super-long life and minimal power consumption. Innovative Cooling Concept The split fan inlet of the Dark Power 13 1000W is a custom-shaped funnel that increases airflow while reducing unwanted turbulence. The wire-free design inside allows the cool air to reach all components flawlessly which ultimately leads to a longer lifespan. Ready for Overclocking Dark Power 13 1000W is particularly suitable for overclocking. The overclocking key gives you full overclocking control by manually switching between the default four 12V-rail mode and the alternative massive single-rail operation.

World Class Topology World Class Topology With an active rectifier and full bridge LLC technology Dark Power 13 1000W offers some of the most advanced technologies available, resulting in higher efficiency, better regulation and lower ripple noise for an incomparably stable operation. Japanese 105°Capacitors Only the best components are used in Dark Power 13 750W. That is why we have exclusively built high-quality Japanese capacitors into the PSU chassis. They are rated to 105°C which ensures stability, reliability, and a long operating life. Highest Convenience and Best Connectivity Modular, sleeved cables of up to 120cm in length simplify component installation and reduce annoying clutter. This results in increased airflow and improved cooling in even the largest PC cases.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really good, quiet 1000 Watt power supply
reviews.reviewText: This power supply has all the modern capabilities that a modern, ATX 3.0 Power Supply should have. It is energy-saving and very quiet.Pros* Includes all Cables* Settable to Single rail or 4 rail for 12 Volt outputs* Very Quiet* Titanium Efficiency* 12VHPWR connector cable ATX 3.0 for newest GPUs* 10-year manufacturer’s warranty* 1000 Watts will easily power just about anything, including a AMD 7950X CPU, and a NVidia 4090 GPU of my rig* modular cables at Power Supply end don't use as many pins, meaning they are not as crowded on the back side of the power supply* No RGB lights (if you don't like lighting)Cons* modular cables at Power Supply end are not standard, meaning a failed cable is harder to replace* Supply has an inrush (starting) current of 51 Amps (using 120 Volt), and that might make some overly sensitive 15 Amp circuit breakers trip unexpectedly when turning on the computer, but is unlikely* 12VHPWR connector cable ATX 3.0 for newest GPUs is hard to bend enough to clear case for at least some Nvidia 4090 GPUs* No USB data connector to get data about temperature, voltage outputs and to control and sense power supply's fan speed* No RGB lights (If you like lighting)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What the name says, QUIET
reviews.reviewText: If you're purchasing this as a replacement or as a new addition to a build, leave your worries behind.This thing delivers all the power you need and stays quiet even with the fan running. I've had no issues with it so far, the setup is straightforward if you've ever installed a power supply on a computer before. Pretty much plug and play. It comes with all the cords you might need and the packaging is very well done.I upgraded and went for a PS that was slightly more than what I needed, no matter which level you choose, I think this company stands behind their product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great, Trustworthy Power Supply
reviews.reviewText: Be quiet has been making excellent power supplies for quite some time. My last PSU was a 1300w BeQuiet that took a turn for the worst due to a power surge. I went ahead and replaced it with a 1000w unit. It was fantastic to simply swap the new power supply in without changing cables. Happy with the purchase and will continue use BeQuiet for years to come.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice PCIe PSU
reviews.reviewText: Super fast delivery by seller. Placed order and received next day. Package came in nice clean organized big box and protected by columns in the box. PSU box was sealed. Everything came as it said in the box. Manual, cables, OC switch, etc... As for the PSU, it works as expected. Quiet with no coil noise so far but had it for only on day. Efficient? Do not know. Just know that it works without any problems. PCIe 5.0 cable fits my 4070ti perfectly. Hope it lasts without problems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No noise issues
reviews.reviewText: Was worried hearing about all of the talk on this unit making some annoying scraping sound when the psu wasn't under load, I went ahead and bought it anyway. Happy to say I can't hear any noise coming from the psu. Felt the need to write this review to hopefully dissuade any decisions made based on the fan noise a lot of people had issues with before.
